Hard work. That is the answer. Harvey is the best closer in New York City and he didnot get there by relaxing.
 When he came to the firm he dominated people thought he worked 100 hours a day so that now he can do what he likes.
 He was 5th in his class in Harvard and that is no easy task. No one can best Harvey so if you want to reach the same level as him you are going to have to work as hard as you can in order to get there.
 I wish you the best of luck as I am going to do the same.
